 Opinions are like...<br><br>Technically Drack is right.  If you are first to engage, or if the mob engages you, then you are entitled to kill it.  If someone else kills it then they have ks'ed you.  If you have logs they will most likely get a stern warning from GM's/guides.<br><br>What is at stake here is how we as a self policing comunity define a camp.  This is not just a problem with outdoor zones, though they are obviously more grey than a zone with well defined camps established by the server community.  The Ancient Cyclops in OOT is a WELL established out door camp, as are quite a few other fixed spawns.  Walking up and taking a spawned AC from a caster who is medding to kill it would result in ZERO warning from a GM, though you would quickly be villafied by the community.  Flipping it around to another extreme, the Hunter/Forager spawn cycle in Traks teeth is a camp of basically an entire zone.  The frogs are aggro, and will attack you for just being there - and all the things on the spawn cycle wander most of the zone, however it is still quite comon for a group to call these spawns 'camped'.  So let me ask the community a few questions, and I'll give my answers as well as to what 'we' feel is an acceptable camp.<br><br>Camp<br>1. The ground or spot on which tents, huts, etc., are erected for shelter<br><br>A single static spawn?  Definitely a camp in my mind.<br><br>A room and the spawns in that room?  A camp.<br><br>The area immediately surrounding it? Starts getting fuzzy here...  Seb is really an example that stands out.  The frogs just outside the Gang get killed alot by people not in the gang... as do all kinds of frogs just outside all of the camps in Seb, where pulling is typically very aggressive.  I's say NO.<br><br>Fixed spawns in a open area.  Campable, even though there is no 'room', as long as the camp is of a small fixed area it should be respected.  Aviaks in SK, Tizmaks in GD all have a few spots with fixed spawns.  I'd respect a group that was sitting near these spawns and obviously pulling them.<br><br>Wandering spawns in an area of a zone?  (Hill giants or what not)  Nope, but I personally don't typically like to compete with another group over a small number of spawns.  I'd probably check out something else, but I don't think this is a camp.<br><br>A wandering random spawn over a whole zone? (Hunter/Forager) I'd say no as well... though I would respect somebodies need for quest pieces.  I would probably help them, but I still don't recognize it as a camp.<br><br>Maybe you can think of a few more types of camps that are called out by players, but that we as a community may or may not recognize as the definative 'camp'.  Let's not flame to much. <p><BR>Kliff Steel<BR><BR>Knight of Brell<BR><BR>Invictorum<BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/usoukyan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Soukyan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#778899>(4/2/02 4:50:12 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1491.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Screenshots you say?</span><hr size=1> Screw camps. That's the biggest downfall of this game. The putz who can sit for 12 hours straight waiting for a mob gets it. If I wander by and it happens to randomly pop up and I need it, I'm gonna kill it. So if you're sitting on the ground waiting for a mob, you better be on your toes. I'll play the game as it was meant to be played. If I'm on a dungeon crawl and you are &quot;camping&quot; a place that's on my path to get further down into a dungeon, you better believe I'm gonna wipe out any mobs that are in my path. So if your camp isn't cleared when I come through, I'll be clearing it to continue through. Now granted, if I never need to pass your &quot;camp&quot; to get to my goal, I obviously won't be a bother to you. <br><br>I have precious little leisure time and I like to make the most of it. If I log on and see a quest mob that I need and nobody is attacking it, I will kill it. Here's where the breakdown in logic occurs. The majority of this community will say that if some player was &quot;camping&quot; (a.k.a. placing one's avatar at known spawn point for several days) that quest mob for four days, he/she is entitled to the kill and not myself who happened to sign on and be there at the right time. I disagree. I could say that I am just as entitled, but because I have a job and a real world life with responsibilities and priorities, I am not entitled to kill that mob? LOL Bulls h i t. I just chose to spend my time doing something other than waiting an insane amount of time to kill a mob that won't spawn for another huge amount of time.<br><br>Verant says that whoever engages it, gets it. Why? Because that was the idea in the first place. For people to have random mobs pop up that they needed for quests. But &quot;powergamers&quot; who have the time to waste in-game have ruined this for every other type of player. (Of course I do believe that the timers for respawns on some quest mobs have been made too long, but that is because they had to compensate for powergamers again) So you can love me or hate me and call me a camp-stealer or whatever, but this whole camping bit is crap. Perhaps Verant should take a hint from Mythic and start giving &quot;camp bonus&quot;. Reward people for moving around and hunting and give less experience for overcamped mobs. After all, just because you sit on your ass in a chair playing doesn't mean your avatar has to mimic you.<br><br>Think about it. Sitting in a stationary spot in &lt;insert zone here&gt; pulling mobs to the group, all the while saying, &quot;We shall vanquish the &lt;insert zone name here&gt; of all of the evil mobs that inhabit it!&quot;  when you know damn well the spawn will not run out. Yeah... we're roleplaying now... woot! Hold me back. LOL Do I have a skewed viewpoint? Maybe. Do alot of other players? Most definitely. Is this really roleplaying? Not entirely. *shrug* Just some thoughts. Maybe this should be in the rants section. I like it better here though. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>~Soukyan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uthistlebane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thistlebane</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Threatening Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(4/2/02 6:04:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1491.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Screenshots you say?</span><hr size=1> Kliff, could you please spell &quot;ingage&quot; properly?  Thanks <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/unexc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nexc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Dubious Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(4/2/02 6:53:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1491.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>