rap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/usoukyan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Soukyan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scowling Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(4/2/02 7:21:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1491.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Screenshots you say?</span><hr size=1> Nexc, that is not a correct analogy.<br><br>I do not cut in line when waiting for something. But within the world of Norrath, there are no rules governing the completion of quests. The unfortunate problem is that being a massive multiplayer game results in many people doing the same quest. Those who can waste their time sitting behind a computer playing a game are rewarded. I don't agree with that. So maybe Verant needs to put in an &quot;Express Checkout&quot;. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br><br>But seriously, If another group of people is crawling through a dungeon, of course I will go elsewhere or I will join them for adventure. But if a bunch of people are sitting around and I want to crawl through the dungeon to the end to find the treasure, of course I am going to fight my way through. Help me or get out of the way. EQ does not exactly have a political system in place for Player Characters so you can't exactly roleplay using that aspect. Essentially, we're a bunch of so-called roleplayers playing the camp game. There's no need to sit around and there's no need to walk eggshells. <br><br>A person waiting in-game for a long time for something makes them no more worthy of getting the item than a person of the same level/status waiting out of game and logging in when the time is right. Both people worked equally as hard to get where they are, but they both got there in different ways. Of course, the powergamers will violently defend their territory saying that if you spend the most time in-game, you should be rewarded. They have to defend themselves and their game. After all, they pay... out wait... the same every month as I do. *shrug* Sounds to me like everyone is equally entitled to items in-game. Even Verant says that.<br><br>Now to clarify: being a nice person, I am not prone to stealing quest mobs from people who have been waiting longer than I. Nor am I apt to KS your camp. I try to avoid those situations at all costs. But it is not out of the realm of possibility for it to happen. It's a cut-throat game. It mimics real life. The world doesn't stop for you and time waits for no man. So next time you are KSed, suck it up and move on. Life's not fair and neither is EverQuest. <br><br>~Soukyan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/uwalknot.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Walknot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Indifferent Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(4/2/02 8:30:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1491.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Screenshots you say?</span><hr size=1> I usually go by the roaming rule.  If it roams it cant be camped.  If its static then I will respect that persons &quot;camp&quot;<br><br>Now, that being said, I will contest outdoor exp spawns, and some inside as well.  (there are a few areas in Seb that could go either way depending on what camp you are at.<br><br>Areas which are FFA Exp that I have come across:<br>HG's<br>SF's<br>Giant fort in BW<br>Giant fort in FM<br>FG<br>ME (cheif gets ganked a lot)<br>UP (for the most part)<br>DSP<br>Orc Fort in EW.<br>Giant Fort EW and GD<br><br>Theses are just a few places where I have found it to be FFA more then a camp.<br><br> <p>WalkNot SoSoftly<br><br> Heyokah Duhara<br>"I am not sunshine, I am dark and grey, for this life of sins I live, each day I pay".</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f7f7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ubrahmindorchadas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brahmin Dorchadas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amiable Poster</span><br> <font color=#778899>(4/2/02 8:45:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1491.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_thumbsup.gif" align=absmiddle>  /agree Danaelle</span><hr size=1> Dirty joker... <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showMessageRange?topicID=1491.topic&start=21&stop=23>2</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showPrevMessage?topicID=1491.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showNextMessage?topicID=1491.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1491.topic&index=20><img src=http://www.ichuu.com/AddReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/finnoruukserverfrm3.emailToFriend?topicID=1491.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://